DirectionUsageRule::State Class Referencefinal

Detailed Description

Semantic state of the DirectionUsageRule.

A State describes the current usage semantics of the lane section. This includes which direction traffic is allowed to travel on the lane and the severity of this restriction.

◆ Severity

enum Severity
strong
Enumerator
kStrict 

No vehicle should travel on this lane in violation of this rule.

kPreferred 

Vehicles should avoid travelling against this rule but certain exceptions apply.

E.g. passing is allowed.

◆ Type

enum Type
strong

Type of allowed travel on the lane.

Categorized based on travel with or against the central axis (+S) of the lane frame.

Enumerator
kWithS 

Travel should proceed in the direction of the +S axis.

kAgainstS 

Travel should proceed opposite the +S axis direction.

kBidirectional 

Travel is allowed both with the lane direction(+S) or against it.

kBidirectionalTurnOnly 

Travel is allowed both with the lane direction(+S) or against it but should be limited in duration, e.g.

when approaching turns.

kNoUse 

Travel on this lane is prohibited.

kParking 

This lane is used to define a parking area.

kUndefined 

There is no defined direction of travel on this lane.
